Chuck,

This one I can help you with--easy

I saw on public TV a guy who could get any stain out of anything---(  I
never saw him get super glue out of anything )
anyway I did see him get a crayon stain out of an item.

Lay an old t-shirt over the stain, and wave the hot iron over the
shirt--it will lift and transfer the crayon spot right out of the
material in question  into the t-shirt.

Give that a shot---

Have fun---

Terry


